---
source: tests/test_help.rs
assertion_line: 49
expression: "normalize_output(&output, temp_dir.path(), &date)"
---
$ govctl work tick --help
Tick acceptance criteria item

Usage: govctl work tick [OPTIONS] <ID> <FIELD> [PATTERN]

Arguments:
  <ID>
          Artifact ID

  <FIELD>
          Field path

  [PATTERN]
          Pattern to match

Options:
      --at <AT>
          Match by index

  -C, --config <CONFIG>
          Path to govctl config (TOML)

      --dry-run
          Dry run: preview changes without writing files

      --exact
          Exact match

      --regex
          Regex pattern

  -s, --status <STATUS>
          New status

          Possible values:
          - done:      Mark work items as done
          - pending:   Mark work items as pending
          - cancelled: Mark work items as cancelled
          
          [default: done]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

EXAMPLES:
    govctl work tick WI-<DATE>-001 acceptance_criteria "Criterion 1"
    govctl work tick WI-<DATE>-001 acceptance_criteria --at 0 -s cancelled

NOTES:
    - Valid work-item statuses are `done`, `pending`, and `cancelled`.
    - Omitting `-s/--status` defaults to `done`.
exit: 0
